cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper proposes a spiking hierarchical model for object recognition which utilizes biologically inspired neural networks. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper focuses on object recognition using vision sensors and achieving high accuracy in recognition tasks. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a new approach to visual computation that can find application in other sensory modalities and computational tasks. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a new approach to object recognition that utilizes precise timing information and can simplify computation. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the asynchronous nature of the vision sensors and how it frees computation and communication from rigid timing constraints, which can be relevant to systems and control.
